  - No canonical `/help` or `/reviews` route exists in `AppRoutes.jsx`, even though `src/pages/UserSetting/sidebar.jsx` links both destinations
- Current web API ownership for the scoped run:
  - `src/api/publicPackagesApi.js` now owns the shared public package transport used by `homepageApi.js`, `listingApi.js`, `packageDetailApi.js`, and `Wishlist`
  - `src/api/bookingApi.js` owns authenticated booking list/detail/create/delete plus v1 payment and passport mutations
  - `src/api/profileApi.js` and `src/api/walletApi.js` own `/api/v1/users/me/profile/`, `/api/v1/users/me/address/`, and `/api/v1/users/me/wallet/*`
  - `src/api/supportApi.js` owns the v1 review, complaint, request, current-user support list, and objection-response endpoints, but Phase 0 found no live page or feature imports yet
  - `src/api/apiService.js` still exports duplicate legacy `/bookings/*` support helpers and overlapping package helpers; this is the main removal/migration candidate for the next phase
