+#### Notes From Implementation
+- The previous `OperatorResponse` logic treated completed/closed bookings as generic under-review states, which would have kept the real review flow hidden even after wiring the API. Phase 3 corrected that status presentation before adding the review action.
+- The objection branch is now modeled as an active support state instead of a hard cancellation state, matching the backend contract that allows the user to upload a response document and move the booking back to `Pending`.
+- `/messages` remained untouched by design because the backend `chat` API is still admin-only and not safe to wire into the authenticated traveler panel as part of this bounded batch.
+
+#### Verification
+- Route tracing:
+  - `/help` now resolves through `AppRoutes.jsx`
+  - `sidebar.jsx` and `Header.js` both route users to the live support destination instead of dead review/help pages
+- Consumer tracing:
+  - `supportApi.js` is now imported by `help.jsx` and `operatorresponse.jsx`
+  - removed support helper exports in `apiService.js` still have zero remaining consumers
+- Runtime verification:
+  - `cd /Users/macbook/Desktop/Huz/Huz-Web-Frontend && npm run build`
+  - Result: success with only pre-existing warnings (`caniuse-lite` age warning plus unrelated unused imports in `PackageDetailPage/components/LeftColumn/Itinerary.js`)
+- Backend verification remains deferred to the later batch because the test-environment blocker (`BE-ENV-001`) is still open and no backend code changed in this phase.
+
